oquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":27,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Agnes Huntercombe was born about 1355, in Holme Lacy, Herefordshire, England, her father, John Huntercombe, was 33 and her mother, Christiana Huntercombe, was 33. She had at least 2 sons and 1 daughter with Philip Scudamore. She died on 14 May 1411, in her hometown, at the age of 57."},"et":{"about 1355–14 May 1411":"umbes 1355–14. mai 1411","1344–1368":"1344–1368","1348–1402":"1348–1402","1355–1411":"1355–1411","1356–Female":"1356–Surnud","1348–1419":"1348–1419","1383–1430":"1383–1430","1389–1442":"1389–1442","1395–1485":"1395–1485","1324–1369":"1324–1369","1324–1361":"1324–1361","1395":"1395","1361":"1361","1383":"1383","1382":"1382","14 May 1411":"14. mai 1411","1348":"1348","1369":"1369","1402":"1402","1324":"1324","1368":"1368","1389":"1389","1356":"1356","1411":"1411","1355":"1355","1344":"1344","1442":"1442","1485":"1485","1430":"1430","about 1355":"umbes 1355","1419":"1419","about 1395":"umbes 1395","Betchworth, Surrey, England":"Betchworth, Surrey, England","Holme Lacy, Herefordshire, England":"Holme Lacy, Herefordshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1355–14 May 1411":"noin 1355–14. toukokuuta 1411","1344–1368":"1344–1368","1348–1402":"1348–1402","1355–1411":"1355–1411","1356–Female":"1356–Kuollut","1348–1419":"1348–1419","1383–1430":"13